  <description><![CDATA[<p>Set on a sunny terrace above the Rhône valley, Crans-Montana enjoys stunning views across the peaks of the Valais region, and offers an excellent variety of skiing and snowboarding to cater for all ages and abilities. The well-linked ski area is accessible by several cable cars from the villages and the free shuttle service carries guests quickly to the key lift stations. The majority of pistes are blues and reds – wide-open runs that are a delight for intermediates. The Plaine Morte glacier at an altitude of 3,000m is not to be missed for the more challenging runs and panoramic views of the Alps. With a friendly and laid-back atmosphere, the resort is great for beginners, who will benefit from the nursery slopes in the resorts 'Snow Island' or at Arnouva. Mountain restaurants are plentiful offering local and international cuisine, whilst non-skiers can also enjoy a vast array of winter-walking, cross-country or après-ski activities.<br /><br />For a taste of skiing in Crans Montana this winter, watch <a rel="noopener noreferrer" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=5e2-oUtaL0I&amp;list=PL9QsC_pOE7lT9j39eLstSbqQmKag3N3mq&amp;index=1" target="_blank" title="Crans Montana Winter Teaser">Crans Montana's winter teaser here</a>.</p>]]></description>
