  <generalInformation><![CDATA[<p><strong>Beginners skiing in Crans Montana <br /></strong></p>
<p>Crans Montana boats several excellent ski schools and good nursery slopes within the resort itself at Snow Island and on the mountain’s gently carving blue runs where wide open runs provide optimal conditions for learning. Ski schools meet either at the bottom of the Bibi Express lift at Snow Island or the mid-station of the Signal cable car.</p>
<p><strong>Intermediates skiing in Crans Montana </strong></p>
<p>The ski area is perfect for intermediate skiers with an excellent selection of blue and red runs covering almost 125km of piste. For more challenging runs and to enjoy one of the longest pistes, skiers should head to the Plaine Morte Glacier at 3,000m to enjoy a 12km run down to Barzettes.</p>
<p><strong>Advanced skiing in Crans Montana </strong></p>
<p>Advanced skiers have a selection of off-piste runs and a selection of black runs. Not to be missed is the National - which stages the Men’s World Cup Downhill. Ski schools within the resort also offer race training.</p>
<p><strong>Snowboarding in Crans Montana </strong></p>
<p>Boarders have the "Space Adrenalin" Snow Park with half pipe, boardercross, jumps and rails but the terrain across the mountain provides plentiful surfing ground for just cruising or practicing your tricks.</p>]]></generalInformation>
